          <article id="perfbuild" class="bg-white border-b border-[--color-border]">

            <header class="flex items-start justify-between px-8 py-5 border-b border-[--color-border] flex-wrap gap-3">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="text-xs font-bold text-[--color-border] font-mono">20</span>
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-0.5">
                  <h5 class="m-0">Performance & Build Tooling</h5>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[--color-caption] m-0">The site-wide setup that ships every clone with PageSpeed-friendly defaults.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-[--color-primary] bg-[--color-accent] px-3 py-1 rounded-[--radius-badge] uppercase tracking-wide self-start">Performance</span>
            </header>

            <div class="px-8 py-6 flex flex-col gap-6">

              <div class="p-4 bg-[--color-accent] border-l-4 border-[--color-primary] rounded-[--radius-card]">
                <p class="m-0 text-sm text-[--color-body] leading-relaxed">
                  <strong>Plain English:</strong> Every clinic site has the same speed problems by default — slow images, heavy tracking scripts, deploy errors. The template solves all of them up front so each new client starts at 90+ on PageSpeed without bespoke work.
                </p>
              </div>

              <!-- 1. Cloudflare adapter patch -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
                <p class="text-xs font-bold text-[--color-caption] uppercase tracking-widest m-0">1. Cloudflare adapter patch (deploy-blocker fix)</p>
                <p class="m-0 text-sm text-[--color-body]">
                  Cloudflare Pages refuses to deploy if any binding is named <code class="code-label">ASSETS</code> (it's reserved). The Astro adapter hardcodes that name in 5 files. Our patch script renames every occurrence to <code class="code-label">STATIC_ASSETS</code> automatically after every install.
                </p>
                <div class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]">
                  <p class="m-0 text-xs text-[--color-body]"><code class="code-label">scripts/patch-cloudflare-adapter.mjs</code> — wired to <code class="code-label">npm postinstall</code>. Idempotent (safe to re-run).</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- 2. Image scripts -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-[--color-border] pt-5">
                <p class="text-xs font-bold text-[--color-caption] uppercase tracking-widest m-0">2. Image optimisation</p>
                <ul class="list-none p-0 m-0 flex flex-col gap-2">
                  <li class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]"><strong class="text-sm text-[--color-headline]">npm run resize-images</strong> <span class="text-xs text-[--color-caption]">— resizes any oversized .webp to a max dimension (default 1920px), in-place re-encode at quality 82 using sharp.</span></li>
                  <li class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]"><strong class="text-sm text-[--color-headline]">Dual hero preload</strong> <span class="text-xs text-[--color-caption]">— BaseLayout accepts both <code class="code-label">heroImage</code> (desktop) and <code class="code-label">heroImageMobile</code>. Each device only fetches the variant it paints.</span></li>
                  <li class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]"><strong class="text-sm text-[--color-headline]">All images .webp</strong> <span class="text-xs text-[--color-caption]">— with explicit width/height, decoding="async", lazy by default, eager only for above-the-fold heroes.</span></li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <!-- 3. Cache headers -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-[--color-border] pt-5">
                <p class="text-xs font-bold text-[--color-caption] uppercase tracking-widest m-0">3. Cache headers (public/_headers)</p>
                <p class="m-0 text-sm text-[--color-body]">Cloudflare Pages auto-purges on every deploy, so 1-year caches are safe even on non-content-hashed paths.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
                  {[
                    { path: "/_astro/*", ttl: "1 year, immutable" },
                    { path: "/images/*", ttl: "1 year + stale-while-revalidate" },
                    { path: "/videos/*", ttl: "1 year + stale-while-revalidate" },
                    { path: "/fonts/*",  ttl: "1 year, immutable" },
                    { path: "/icons/*",  ttl: "1 year, immutable" },
                    { path: "/*.svg",    ttl: "7 days" },
                  ].map(c => (
                    <div class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card] flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
                      <code class="code-label shrink-0">{c.path}</code>
                      <span class="text-xs text-[--color-body]">{c.ttl}</span>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- 4. Deferred GTM -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-[--color-border] pt-5">
                <p class="text-xs font-bold text-[--color-caption] uppercase tracking-widest m-0">4. Deferred GTM loader</p>
                <p class="m-0 text-sm text-[--color-body]">GTM saves 150–220 KB of JS by loading on idle, first user interaction, or 6-second fallback (Safari). Final move post-launch: migrate to Cloudflare Zaraz (zero browser JS).</p>
              </div>

              <!-- 5. Site-wide rules -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-[--color-border] pt-5">
                <p class="text-xs font-bold text-[--color-caption] uppercase tracking-widest m-0">5. Site-wide rules</p>
                <ul class="list-none p-0 m-0 flex flex-col gap-2">
                  <li class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]"><code class="code-label">&lt;html lang="en-GB"&gt;</code> <span class="text-xs text-[--color-caption]">— UK targeting, British screen-reader voice, British spellcheck.</span></li>
                  <li class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]"><strong class="text-sm">noindex default = true</strong> <span class="text-xs text-[--color-caption]">— template ships in noindex mode. Flip to false ONLY when the user says "go live".</span></li>
                  <li class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]"><strong class="text-sm">robots.txt is ASCII-only</strong> <span class="text-xs text-[--color-caption]">— Cloudflare serves it without charset; box-drawing characters cause mojibake.</span></li>
                  <li class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]"><strong class="text-sm">_redirects status codes</strong> <span class="text-xs text-[--color-caption]">— only 200/301/302/303/307/308 work on Pages. 404/410 need a Pages Function.</span></li>
                  <li class="p-3 bg-[--color-muted] border border-[--color-border] rounded-[--radius-card]"><strong class="text-sm">CSP includes media-src 'self'</strong> <span class="text-xs text-[--color-caption]">— required for self-hosted hero video.</span></li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <!-- 6. Targets -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-[--color-border] pt-5">
                <p class="text-xs font-bold text-[--color-caption] uppercase tracking-widest m-0">6. Core Web Vitals targets</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
                  {[
                    { metric: "LCP", target: "< 2.5s", note: "Largest Contentful Paint (hero image load)" },
                    { metric: "CLS", target: "< 0.1",  note: "Layout Shift (no jumping content)" },
                    { metric: "INP", target: "< 200ms", note: "Interaction responsiveness" },
